Merge pull request #11 from ppolewicz/compatiblity_with_2.6

Restore compatibility with python 2.6

Restore compatibility with python 2.6

63895ec09d5e28f4c3a308c737503c61e4e3bb43 accidentally broke python 2.6
compatibility due to usage of OrderedDict, which is not available
in the collections module in that version.

Possible fixes were:
1. Skip defining FrozenOrderedDict when running 2.6
2. Depend on ordereddict module when running 2.6 and import it when
needed
3. Copy OrderedDict recipe and use it when needed
4. Do not provide FrozenOrderedDict on 2.6

the last one was chosen due to maintainer preference to keep the code
base compact.
fix memory explosion, much faster version.
